ADIn the wake of Tuesday’s strike, Pakistani Prime Minister Imran Khan called an emergency meeting of top security and government officials.
The operation also came just weeks before national elections in India, where Modi — a hawk on matters of national security — is seeking a second term.
India and Pakistan often trade artillery fire across the Line of Control in Kashmir, the Himalayan region they both claim.
India accuses Pakistan of supporting militants who fight against Indian rule in Kashmir and launch attacks elsewhere in India.
ADShaiq Hussain in Islamabad, Pakistan; Haq Nawaz Khan in Peshawar, Pakistan; and Ishfaq Naseem in Srinagar, India, contributed to this report.